subject: World Cup (Skiing)
lead_paragraph: Elisabeth Görgl of Austria won a World Cup giant slalom in Maribor, Slovenia, for the first victory of her career. Görgl, who led after the first leg, finished in a two-run combined time of 2:38.49. Manuela Moelgg of Italy took second, 0.49 behind, and Denise Karbon of Italy finished third.
